title: THERE it is! Rep. DeLauro dials the Dems’ health reform fear mongering up to eleven
text:
THERE it is! Rep. DeLauro dials the Dems’ health reform fear mongering up to eleven Posted at 12:47 pm on March 24, 2017 by Doug P. Share on Facebook Share on Twitter 
Remember when Rep. Alan Grayson said in 2009 that the Republican health care plan was “if you get sick, die quickly” and ads in 2012 depicting Paul Ryan pushing “grandma” off a cliff? Rep. Laura DeLauro took a page from that approach and ran with it today: . @rosadelauro : "What does the GOP stand for? 'Get Old People.' That's what this bill does." pic.twitter.com/9ekkg0Nr5I 
— Fox News (@FoxNews) March 24, 2017 
Well there’s a well reasoned “argument.” @FoxNews @rosadelauro Don't you have an obligation to not be insane? How did this woman escape? 
— Mike Wall (@wallwriting) March 24, 2017 Liberals are so predictable! https://t.co/3V6rw6w6EX
